Spent its working life at Cawdor Quarry, Matlock in Derbyshire. Was rescued by Brian Roberts, of Tollerton, Nottinghamshire, who later sold it to Pete Clark who named it ‘Fulstow’ after the village where he lives in Lincolnshire. It now works on the Lincolnshire Wolds Railway, where it has recently undergone its first ten-yearly overhaul.
